strings.string: This is a scope 4 FPT file. It contains functional profile templates.
This LonMark Device Resource FPT file was created by Echelon Corporation. Contact us at 408-938-5200 or at www.echelon.com on the internet.
The demand calculated duct static pressure setpoint subject to limits.

Level percent. SNVT_switch should be used instead of SNVT_lev_percent, with the exception of network variables that are used to communicate a percentage value and that require the additional resolution provided by SNVT_lev_percent; or for network variable members of functional profiles that are designed primarily for interfacing with SNVT_lev_percent members of other profiles.
The number of designated rouge VAVs.
Used to add a VAV device handle to the Rouge list. Rouges are not used in control sequence.
Used to remove a VAV device handle to the Rouge list.
The index to the rouge list. Zero based.
Reports the Index, and the handle of the last requested nviShowRouge request.
The delay time, default to scene.
Setpoint for default duct static pressure.
Setpoint for maximum duct static pressure.
Setpoint for minimum duct static pressure.
Time period used for a measurement.
Each state is a boolean single bit value. SNVT_state_64 is preferred.
This SNVT is obsolete. Use SNVT_switch instead.
The maximum period of time between consecutive transmissions of the current value.
The minimum period of time between consecutive transmissions of the current value.
The alarm threshold for the running hours counter.
The maximum period of time that may expire with no updates on the associated input network variables before the object goes into heartbeat failure mode. A zero value disables the mechanism.
Used to select master clock or slave clock, non-zero indicates this is master clock.
Switch with scene and setting control.
An enhanced version of SNVT_switch with scene and setting controls similar to SNVT_scene and SNVT_setting.
Used to report alarm status for a functional block or device. Replaces SNVT_alarm.
